{{Main|2003年飓风凯特}}
飓风凯特源于9月25日热带大西洋中部的一股东风波。风暴向西北方向前进，但受[[副热带高压脊|副热带高压脊]]出现薄弱环节的影响转向东进。凯特增强成飓风，并在围绕中层[[低气压|低气压]]移动期间突然向西大幅转向，于10月4日强化成风力时速205公里的大型飓风。风暴之后又围绕[[反气旋|反气旋]]边缘急剧向北转向并逐渐减弱，从[[纽芬兰岛|纽芬兰岛]]以东经过后转变成[[温带气旋|温带气旋]]。这场温带风暴又持续了3天，最终在[[斯堪的纳维亚|斯堪的纳维亚]]附近失去踪影<ref name="katetcr">{{cite web | author = Pasch, Richard J. & Molleda, Robert | year = 2003 | title = Hurricane Kate Tropical Cyclone Report | publisher = National Hurricane Center | accessdate = 2014-07-14 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140714233123/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/2003kate.shtml | archivedate = 2014-07-14 | deadurl = yes | url = http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/2003kate.shtml? }}</ref>。

凯特在[[飓风胡安|飓风胡安]]重创[[新斯科舍|新斯科舍]]仅一周后对[[加拿大大西洋省份|加拿大大西洋省份]]构成威胁，但最终有惊无险，对陆地产生的影响很小，仅限于给纽芬兰岛带去的暴雨和中等强度大风<ref name="katebulletin3">{{cite web | author = Roussel/Bowyer | year = 2003 | title = Canadian Hurricane Information Statement issued by the Canadian Hurricane Centre of Environment Canada at 9:30 AM NDT Monday 06 October 2003 | publisher = Canadian Hurricane Centre | accessdate = 2011-06-11 | url = http://www.atl.ec.gc.ca/weather/hurricane/bulletins/20031006121000.Kate.txt.en | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110611121614/http://www.atl.ec.gc.ca/weather/hurricane/bulletins/20031006121000.Kate.txt.en | archivedate = 2011-06-11 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。[[圣约翰斯_(纽芬兰-拉布拉多)|圣约翰斯]]在10月6日记录下45毫米降水，创下当地在每年这一天中降雨量的新纪录<ref name="cbcnews">{{cite news | author = CBC news | title = Lots of rain, but no flooding from Kate | accessdate = 2008-12-04 | archivedate = 2008-12-04 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081204120502/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/newfoundland-labrador/story/2003/10/07/nf_kate_20031007.html | url = http://www.cbc.ca/canada/newfoundland-labrador/story/2003/10/07/nf_kate_20031007.html | work = CBC News | date = 2003-10-07 }}</ref>。此外，凯特与北面的[[高气压|高气压区]]相互影响，给北卡罗莱纳州和新英格兰沿海带去约1米高的海浪<ref name="surfline">{{cite press release | author = Sean Collins and the Surfline Forecast Team | year = 2003 | title = Wavetraks October 2003 Newsletter}}</ref>。
